There were no princesses in Poland since 1921

The title was given by the Holy Roman Emporer, not Poland. The courtesy title of prince, in this case princess, was recognised by Queen Elizabeth II because the family was no longer living in Poland, they were living in the UK. So the family needed the permission from the Queen. Stop removing the princess title it has nothing to do with Poland, the UK does have nobility.
HRE no longer exists. Poland no longer recognizes nobility titles. This person is not British.
